'We stayed at this hotel at the end of October. We were there for the start of the Volvo Ocean Race. We were hardly in the hotel except to sleep. I agree with the other reviews about the rooms being very dated and needing major upgrades. The views however were spectacular, and the locations was about as good as I could imagine for Alicante. Carla, who worked at the front desk was about as sweet a person as you will find. Extremely helpful and pleasant, and a big asset to the hotel. Room Tip: Higher floors, view of the marina. Corner rooms have best view, but are smallest. Bring earplugs (ev... See more room tips'